text: An election happened on November 3, 2020 to elect a Senator from Alabama. The two people in the election were Doug Jones (Democratic Party) and Tommy Tuberville (Republican Party). Tuberville won the election with 60.2% of the vote. He became a Senator on January 3, 2021 when he was sworn in. ==Democratic Party primary== Nobody in the Democratic Party went against Doug Jones in the primary, so no vote happened. ==Republican Party primary== Six people were in the Republican Party primary. Tommy Tuberville won the runoff. ==Results== ==References== Category:21st century in Alabama Category:2020 United States Senate elections
title: 2020 United States Senate election in Alabama
